The 1996 [[Embassy (cigarette)|Embassy]] [[World Snooker Championship]] professional [[Snooker world rankings|ranking]] [[snooker]] tournament took place at the [[Crucible Theatre]], [[Sheffield]] between 20 April<U+2013>6 May 1996.

[[Stephen Hendry]] won in the final 18<U+2013>12 against [[Peter Ebdon]].

==Tournament summary==
* In the first round {{cuegloss|match}} between [[Ronnie O'Sullivan]] and [[Alain Robidoux]], Robidoux accused O'Sullivan of not showing him due respect by playing left-handed for almost a {{cuegloss|frame}},<ref name="O'Sullivan vs. Robidoux">{{Cite news |author=Sportsmail |title=Balotelli's backheel and five others who failed to show some R-E-S-P-E-C-T! |date=25 July 2011 |work=Daily Mail  |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/article-2018496/VIDEO-Mario-Balotelli-backheel-disrespectful-sports-stars.html |accessdate=3 November 2011 |location=London}}</ref> and refused to shake hands with him when the match ended.<ref>{{cite web|title=Anger over left-leaning O'Sullivan|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/sport/anger-over-leftleaning-osullivan-1306125.html|publisher=[[The Independent]]|accessdate=11 May 2012}}</ref> O'Sullivan reacted to this by claiming that "I'm better with my left hand than he was with his right".<ref name="O'Sullivan vs. Robidoux"/> O'Sullivan was summoned to a disciplinary hearing in response to Robidoux's formal complaint, where he had to prove that he could play to a high level with his left hand. He played three frames of snooker against former World Championship runner-up [[Rex Williams]], winning all three. The charge of bringing the game into disrepute was subsequently dropped.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/sport/general/snooker-bad-breaks-mount-up-for-a-troubled-soul-428502.html |title=Bad breaks mount up for a troubled soul|work=The Independent |accessdate=5 May 2007|date=15 December 2006| location=London}}</ref>
* O'Sullivan also received a two-year suspended ban, plus a <U+00A3>20,000 fine and another <U+00A3>10,000 to be given to charity, for an alleged assault on an official.<ref>{{cite web|last=Talbot|first=Harry|title=Welcome to the boocible|url=http://www.thesun.co.uk/sol/homepage/sport/4279362/Mark-Williams-booed-by-Crucible-fans.html|publisher=[[The Sun (United Kingdom){{!}}The Sun]]|accessdate=11 May 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Bad Boys: Ronnie O'Sullivan|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/other_sports/snooker/2985851.stm|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|accessdate=11 May 2012}}</ref>
* [[Terry Griffiths]] won his first round match for the 14th time in a row since 1983.<ref>{{cite web|title=Terry Griffiths at the World Championships|url=http://www.snookerdatabase.co.uk/PlayerDetails.aspx?PlayerKey=53&tourns=WC&plStat=2#PlayerResults|publisher=Snooker Database|accessdate=11 May 2012}}</ref>  This run of successive first round victories is still a record.<ref>{{cite web|last=Kastner|first=Hugo|title=SNOOKER <U+2013> Spieler, Regeln & Rekorde (May 2011 update)|url=http://www.hugo-kastner.at/snooker_crucible_highlights_mai11.pdf|accessdate=27 May 2012|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/67z1JltuN|archivedate=27 May 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Downer|first=Chris|title=Crucible Almanac|year=2012|pages=119}}</ref>

==Prize fund==
The breakdown of prize money for this year is shown below:<ref name="Snooker.org"/><ref>{{cite book|last=Downer|first=Chris|title=Crucible Almanac|year=2012|pages=130}}</ref>
*Winner: [[Pound sterling|<U+00A3>]]200,000
*Runner-up: <U+00A3>120,000
*Semi-final: <U+00A3>60,000
*Quarter-final: <U+00A3>30,500
*Last 16: <U+00A3>16,000
*Last 32: <U+00A3>9,000

*Highest break: <U+00A3>17,000
*Maximum break: <U+00A3>147,000

*Total: <U+00A3>1,200,000

