== Century breaks ==
There were 48 century breaks in the 1996 World Snooker Championship,<ref name="Snooker.org"/> a new record which would last until [[1988 World Snooker Championship|1998]]. The highest break of the tournament was 144 made by both [[Peter Ebdon]] and [[Tony Drago]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Downer|first=Chris|title=Crucible Almanac|year=2012|pages=148}}</ref> This was only the second time since [[1980 World Snooker Championship|1980]], when [[Kirk Stevens]] and [[Steve Davis]] both made a 136, that two players had the joint highest break of the championship.<ref>{{cite web|title=Crucible Centuries|url=http://www.snooker.org/Plr/wc_centuries.shtml|publisher=Snooker.org|accessdate=3 April 2012}}</ref> Stephen Hendry made 11 century breaks in the tournament,<ref name="Snooker.org"/> one short of his record of 12 set the [[1995 World Snooker Championship|previous year]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Eric|first=Hayton|title=The CueSport Book of Professional Snooker: The Complete Record & History|year=2004|publisher=Rose Villa Publications|location=London|isbn=978-0-9548549-0-4}}</ref>
